This Starbucks is a block away from Union Station and on the way there from the Clinton Blue Line stop. I’ve been going here about three to four times a week and Mary and Trevor never fail to make me smile and have a conversation with me if they have a longer line of people - they are amazing at multitasking! Don’t plan on changing my go to Starbucks anytime soon because this one is one of the best I’ve been to yet!

Some people have a Cheers bar, well I’ve got that every day at this Starbucks. The staff is always in an upbeat mood, able to handle the morning rush and are probably one of the most efficient, yet caring teams I’ve ever seen.  The manager, Kris, is fantastic and empowers her employees to do a stellar job - she also knows how to step in, lead by example and give strategic advice to make sure that everyone on her team rises together to achieve high standards.  All of the baristas they have and specifically Lou, Tamika, Steph, Trevor are committed to making not only a great cup of coffee for you but an experience that is enjoyable. They are personable and always positive.  I’ve been going to this location regularly for the past two years and it is by far the best in Chicago.  - Gary Scott

I'm here everyday weekday. I use my mobile app and my breakfast and coffee are always ready when I arrive. I get basically the same thing everday, Well because their my favorite.  My cold brew with 6 pumps of caramel and cream is perfect everyday!!! And believe me when I say my weekend trips to my neighborhood Starbucks rarely get my iced coffee this good. Kudos to the staff. Seeing them is my first real smile of my day and they make me feel like family.  Thank you Starbuck staff at 550 w Van Buren store in Chicago Illinois ♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️♥️ Robin Hamilton

This recently-renovated Starbucks is one of many in the immediate vicinity, but it regularly features long lines that snake through the shop. The key is to time your coffee break/snack attack around these population explosions. Other than that, I've never had a problem getting a seat. Service is always with a smile, the wifi is strong and consistent, and the foodstuffs are always in stock. Acknowledging it's status as a Starbucks for the busy West Looper, there are no lounging chairs like other Starbucks, but there are a few tables conducive to meeting with others.
Quick service.
Probably the first reviewer caught them on a bad day. Right now, there are a total of 6 baristas and the service is quick. Although I wish my sandwich was more filling.

It has an outdoor seating space in the shade so that's nice in the summer but they do not staff it properly. There is one, maybe two Baristas taking orders and only one making the drink orders. Slower than the usual speedy Starbucks service I've been accustomed to.
